The paper proposes a method for accelerating deep neural networks, which is a common topic in computer vision (cs.CV) and machine learning (cs.LG). The method involves learning the group structure in a fully end-to-end manner, which falls under the category of artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The paper also mentions combining the method with depthwise separable convolution, which is a technique commonly used in neural network optimization (cs.NE). Finally, the paper evaluates the performance of the proposed method on image classification tasks, which is a common application in multimedia (cs.MM).
